Linux on an old MacBook Pro
---

# Introduction
I found an old MacBook Pro hanging around in need of somthing to do.

## Specs
* MacBook Pro 11,1 in Late 2013 spec
* Model: Number A1502
* CPU: intel "i5-4258U" 
* RAM: 8GB "Late 2013"

As it's well out of Apples support Stuck on MacOS 11 for eternity it's basically e-Waste well according to Apple. I however have other plans involving Linux.

# Which Linux?
Reading around it sounds like it should still be capable of running a current Distro as it's 64bit and a resnable spec. I'm a KDE fan and fancy trying out Fedora.

Distro: Fedora 43 KDE flavour

I set the iso file up on a USB pen drive as a live boot.

